As of the census<ref name="census20102">{{cite web |title=U.S. Census website |url=https://www.census.gov |accessdate=25 May 2011 |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref> of 2010, there were 613 people living in the CDP. There were 344 housing units. The [[Race and ethnicity in the United States Census|racial makeup]] of the town was 96.1% White, 0.5% American Indian and Alaska Native, 0.8% Asian, 1.8% from some other race, and 0.8% from two or more races. Hispanic or Latino of any race were 3.6% of the population.
